lational webs to find balance and harmony. The book invites readers to ponder the deep implications of how and why we care and the ways end-of-life care arrangements complicate both living and dying for many elders.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAgeingxSocial aspectszChina. 0aAging parentsxCarezChina. 0aAgingxSocial aspectszChina. 0aGeriatricsxSocial aspectszChina. 0aIntergenerational relationszChina. 0aOlder peoplexCarezChina. 0aOlder peoplexHome carezChina. 0aOlder peoplexServices forzChina. 0aOlder peoplezChina. 0aSocial changezChina. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aChina, Elder Care, New China, Ageism, Anthropology, Cultural Studies, Ethnography, Social History, Urban, Bioethics, Aging, Life, Society, Death, Health, Care Arrangements, History, Children, Family, Parents, Healthcare.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073913840uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197881395340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978813953423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978813953/original  a978-3-11-073913-8  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DSL